Merge sort is a sorting algorithm which use divide and Conquer methodology to sort the element.

Algo
-----------
1. Array of element
2. Check size of element ->if 0 or 1 -> already sorted
3. Size > 1 ->
   1. middle index - min+max/2
   2. temp arrayLeft = mergeSort(array, min, middle) // recursive calling to sort 0 till middle items
   3. temp arrayRight = mergeSort(array, middle+1, max) // recursive calling to sort the middle+1 till last index
   4. Once completed merge arrayLeft and arrayRight to generate final sorted list

Pseudo Code
--------------

function mergeSort(array):
    if length(array) <= 1:
        return array

    mid = length(array) / 2
    leftHalf = mergeSort(array[0:mid])
    rightHalf = mergeSort(array[mid+1:length(array)])

    return merge(leftHalf, rightHalf)
